2476static MZ_FORCEINLINEinline __attribute__((__always_inline__)) void tdefl_record_match(tdefl_compressor *d, mz_uint match_len, mz_uint match_dist)
2477{
2478 mz_uint32 s0, s1;
2479
2480 MZ_ASSERT((match_len >= TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN) && (match_dist >= 1) && (match_dist <= TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE))((void) sizeof (((match_len >= TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN) &&
(match_dist >= 1) && (match_dist <= TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE
)) ? 1 : 0), __extension__ ({ if ((match_len >= TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN
) && (match_dist >= 1) && (match_dist <=
TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE)) ; else __assert_fail ("(match_len >= TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN) && (match_dist >= 1) && (match_dist <= TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE)"
, "/work/repo/external/CppMicroServices/third_party/miniz.c",
2480, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
2481
2482 d->m_total_lz_bytes += match_len;
2483
2484 d->m_pLZ_code_buf[0] = (mz_uint8)(match_len - TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN);
2485
2486 match_dist -= 1;
2487 d->m_pLZ_code_buf[1] = (mz_uint8)(match_dist & 0xFF);
2488 d->m_pLZ_code_buf[2] = (mz_uint8)(match_dist >> 8); d->m_pLZ_code_buf += 3;
2489
2490 *d->m_pLZ_flags = (mz_uint8)((*d->m_pLZ_flags >> 1) | 0x80); if (--d->m_num_flags_left == 0) { d->m_num_flags_left = 8; d->m_pLZ_flags = d->m_pLZ_code_buf++; }
2491
2492 s0 = s_tdefl_small_dist_sym[match_dist & 511]; s1 = s_tdefl_large_dist_sym[(match_dist >> 8) & 127];
2493 d->m_huff_count[1][(match_dist < 512) ? s0 : s1]++;
2494
2495 if (match_len >= TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN) d->m_huff_count[0][s_tdefl_len_sym[match_len - TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN]]++;
2496}
2497
2498static mz_bool tdefl_compress_normal(tdefl_compressor *d)
2499{
2500 const mz_uint8 *pSrc = d->m_pSrc; size_t src_buf_left = d->m_src_buf_left;
2501 tdefl_flush flush = d->m_flush;
2502
2503 while ((src_buf_left) || ((flush) && (d->m_lookahead_size)))
2504 {
2505 mz_uint len_to_move, cur_match_dist, cur_match_len, cur_pos;
2506 // Update dictionary and hash chains. Keeps the lookahead size equal to TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN.
2507 if ((d->m_lookahead_size + d->m_dict_size) >= (TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN - 1))
2508 {
2509 mz_uint dst_pos = (d->m_lookahead_pos + d->m_lookahead_size) & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK, ins_pos = d->m_lookahead_pos + d->m_lookahead_size - 2;
2510 mz_uint hash = (d->m_dict[ins_pos & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK] << TDEFL_LZ_HASH_SHIFT) ^ d->m_dict[(ins_pos + 1) & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK];
2511 mz_uint num_bytes_to_process = (mz_uint)MZ_MIN(src_buf_left, TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN - d->m_lookahead_size)(((src_buf_left)<(TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN - d->m_lookahead_size
))?(src_buf_left):(TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN - d->m_lookahead_size
));
2512 const mz_uint8 *pSrc_end = pSrc + num_bytes_to_process;
2513 src_buf_left -= num_bytes_to_process;
2514 d->m_lookahead_size += num_bytes_to_process;
2515 while (pSrc != pSrc_end)
2516 {
2517 mz_uint8 c = *pSrc++; d->m_dict[dst_pos] = c; if (dst_pos < (TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN - 1)) d->m_dict[TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE + dst_pos] = c;
2518 hash = ((hash << TDEFL_LZ_HASH_SHIFT) ^ c) & (TDEFL_LZ_HASH_SIZE - 1);
2519 d->m_next[ins_pos & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK] = d->m_hash[hash]; d->m_hash[hash] = (mz_uint16)(ins_pos);
2520 dst_pos = (dst_pos + 1) & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK; ins_pos++;
2521 }
2522 }
2523 else
2524 {
2525 while ((src_buf_left) && (d->m_lookahead_size < TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN))
2526 {
2527 mz_uint8 c = *pSrc++;
2528 mz_uint dst_pos = (d->m_lookahead_pos + d->m_lookahead_size) & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK;
2529 src_buf_left--;
2530 d->m_dict[dst_pos] = c;
2531 if (dst_pos < (TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN - 1))
2532 d->m_dict[TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE + dst_pos] = c;
2533 if ((++d->m_lookahead_size + d->m_dict_size) >= TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN)
2534 {
2535 mz_uint ins_pos = d->m_lookahead_pos + (d->m_lookahead_size - 1) - 2;
2536 mz_uint hash = ((d->m_dict[ins_pos & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK] << (TDEFL_LZ_HASH_SHIFT * 2)) ^ (d->m_dict[(ins_pos + 1) & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK] << TDEFL_LZ_HASH_SHIFT) ^ c) & (TDEFL_LZ_HASH_SIZE - 1);
2537 d->m_next[ins_pos & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK] = d->m_hash[hash]; d->m_hash[hash] = (mz_uint16)(ins_pos);
2538 }
2539 }
2540 }
2541 d->m_dict_size = MZ_MIN(TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE - d->m_lookahead_size, d->m_dict_size)(((TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE - d->m_lookahead_size)<(d->m_dict_size
))?(TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE - d->m_lookahead_size):(d->m_dict_size
));
2542 if ((!flush) && (d->m_lookahead_size < TDEFL_MAX_MATCH_LEN))
2543 break;
2544
2545 // Simple lazy/greedy parsing state machine.
2546 len_to_move = 1; cur_match_dist = 0; cur_match_len = d->m_saved_match_len ? d->m_saved_match_len : (TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN - 1); cur_pos = d->m_lookahead_pos & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK;
2547 if (d->m_flags & (TDEFL_RLE_MATCHES | TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_RAW_BLOCKS))
2548 {
2549 if ((d->m_dict_size) && (!(d->m_flags & TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_RAW_BLOCKS)))
2550 {
2551 mz_uint8 c = d->m_dict[(cur_pos - 1) & TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE_MASK];
2552 cur_match_len = 0; while (cur_match_len < d->m_lookahead_size) { if (d->m_dict[cur_pos + cur_match_len] != c) break; cur_match_len++; }
2553 if (cur_match_len < TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN) cur_match_len = 0; else cur_match_dist = 1;
2554 }
2555 }
2556 else
2557 {
2558 tdefl_find_match(d, d->m_lookahead_pos, d->m_dict_size, d->m_lookahead_size, &cur_match_dist, &cur_match_len);
2559 }
2560 if (((cur_match_len == TDEFL_MIN_MATCH_LEN) && (cur_match_dist >= 8U*1024U)) || (cur_pos == cur_match_dist) || ((d->m_flags & TDEFL_FILTER_MATCHES) && (cur_match_len <= 5)))
2561 {
2562 cur_match_dist = cur_match_len = 0;
2563 }
2564 if (d->m_saved_match_len)
2565 {
2566 if (cur_match_len > d->m_saved_match_len)
2567 {
2568 tdefl_record_literal(d, (mz_uint8)d->m_saved_lit);
2569 if (cur_match_len >= 128)
2570 {
2571 tdefl_record_match(d, cur_match_len, cur_match_dist);
2572 d->m_saved_match_len = 0; len_to_move = cur_match_len;
2573 }
2574 else
2575 {
2576 d->m_saved_lit = d->m_dict[cur_pos]; d->m_saved_match_dist = cur_match_dist; d->m_saved_match_len = cur_match_len;
2577 }
2578 }
2579 else
2580 {
2581 tdefl_record_match(d, d->m_saved_match_len, d->m_saved_match_dist);
2582 len_to_move = d->m_saved_match_len - 1; d->m_saved_match_len = 0;
2583 }
2584 }
2585 else if (!cur_match_dist)
2586 tdefl_record_literal(d, d->m_dict[MZ_MIN(cur_pos, sizeof(d->m_dict) - 1)(((cur_pos)<(sizeof(d->m_dict) - 1))?(cur_pos):(sizeof(
d->m_dict) - 1))]);
2587 else if ((d->m_greedy_parsing) || (d->m_flags & TDEFL_RLE_MATCHES) || (cur_match_len >= 128))
2588 {
2589 tdefl_record_match(d, cur_match_len, cur_match_dist);
2590 len_to_move = cur_match_len;
2591 }
2592 else
2593 {
2594 d->m_saved_lit = d->m_dict[MZ_MIN(cur_pos, sizeof(d->m_dict) - 1)(((cur_pos)<(sizeof(d->m_dict) - 1))?(cur_pos):(sizeof(
d->m_dict) - 1))]; d->m_saved_match_dist = cur_match_dist; d->m_saved_match_len = cur_match_len;
2595 }
2596 // Move the lookahead forward by len_to_move bytes.
2597 d->m_lookahead_pos += len_to_move;
2598 MZ_ASSERT(d->m_lookahead_size >= len_to_move)((void) sizeof ((d->m_lookahead_size >= len_to_move) ? 1
: 0), __extension__ ({ if (d->m_lookahead_size >= len_to_move
) ; else __assert_fail ("d->m_lookahead_size >= len_to_move"
, "/work/repo/external/CppMicroServices/third_party/miniz.c",
2598, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); }));
2599 d->m_lookahead_size -= len_to_move;
2600 d->m_dict_size = MZ_MIN(d->m_dict_size + len_to_move, TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE)(((d->m_dict_size + len_to_move)<(TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE))?
(d->m_dict_size + len_to_move):(TDEFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE));
2601 // Check if it's time to flush the current LZ codes to the internal output buffer.
2602 if ( (d->m_pLZ_code_buf > &d->m_lz_code_buf[TDEFL_LZ_CODE_BUF_SIZE - 8]) ||
2603 ( (d->m_total_lz_bytes > 31*1024) && (((((mz_uint)(d->m_pLZ_code_buf - d->m_lz_code_buf) * 115) >> 7) >= d->m_total_lz_bytes) || (d->m_flags & TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_RAW_BLOCKS))) )
2604 {
2605 int n;
2606 d->m_pSrc = pSrc; d->m_src_buf_left = src_buf_left;
2607 if ((n = tdefl_flush_block(d, 0)) != 0)
2608 return (n < 0) ? MZ_FALSE(0) : MZ_TRUE(1);
2609 }
2610 }
2611
2612 d->m_pSrc = pSrc; d->m_src_buf_left = src_buf_left;
2613 return MZ_TRUE(1);
2614}
2615
2616static tdefl_status tdefl_flush_output_buffer(tdefl_compressor *d)
2617{
2618 if (d->m_pIn_buf_size)
2619 {
2620 *d->m_pIn_buf_size = d->m_pSrc - (const mz_uint8 *)d->m_pIn_buf;
2621 }
2622
2623 if (d->m_pOut_buf_size)
2624 {
2625 size_t n = MZ_MIN(*d->m_pOut_buf_size - d->m_out_buf_ofs, d->m_output_flush_remaining)(((*d->m_pOut_buf_size - d->m_out_buf_ofs)<(d->m_output_flush_remaining
))?(*d->m_pOut_buf_size - d->m_out_buf_ofs):(d->m_output_flush_remaining
));
2626 memcpy((mz_uint8 *)d->m_pOut_buf + d->m_out_buf_ofs, d->m_output_buf + d->m_output_flush_ofs, n);
2627 d->m_output_flush_ofs += (mz_uint)n;
2628 d->m_output_flush_remaining -= (mz_uint)n;
2629 d->m_out_buf_ofs += n;
2630
2631 *d->m_pOut_buf_size = d->m_out_buf_ofs;
2632 }
2633
2634 return (d->m_finished && !d->m_output_flush_remaining) ? TDEFL_STATUS_DONE : TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY;
2635}
2636
2637tdefl_status tdefl_compress(tdefl_compressor *d, const void *pIn_buf, size_t *pIn_buf_size, void *pOut_buf, size_t *pOut_buf_size, tdefl_flush flush)
2638{
2639 if (!d)
2640 {
2641 if (pIn_buf_size) *pIn_buf_size = 0;
2642 if (pOut_buf_size) *pOut_buf_size = 0;
2643 return TDEFL_STATUS_BAD_PARAM;
2644 }
2645
2646 d->m_pIn_buf = pIn_buf; d->m_pIn_buf_size = pIn_buf_size;
2647 d->m_pOut_buf = pOut_buf; d->m_pOut_buf_size = pOut_buf_size;
2648 d->m_pSrc = (const mz_uint8 *)(pIn_buf); d->m_src_buf_left = pIn_buf_size ? *pIn_buf_size : 0;
2649 d->m_out_buf_ofs = 0;
2650 d->m_flush = flush;
2651
2652 if ( ((d->m_pPut_buf_func != NULL((void*)0)) == ((pOut_buf != NULL((void*)0)) || (pOut_buf_size != NULL((void*)0)))) || (d->m_prev_return_status != TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY) ||
2653 (d->m_wants_to_finish && (flush != TDEFL_FINISH)) || (pIn_buf_size && *pIn_buf_size && !pIn_buf) || (pOut_buf_size && *pOut_buf_size && !pOut_buf) )
2654 {
2655 if (pIn_buf_size) *pIn_buf_size = 0;
2656 if (pOut_buf_size) *pOut_buf_size = 0;
2657 return (d->m_prev_return_status = TDEFL_STATUS_BAD_PARAM);
2658 }
2659 d->m_wants_to_finish |= (flush == TDEFL_FINISH);
2660
2661 if ((d->m_output_flush_remaining) || (d->m_finished))
2662 return (d->m_prev_return_status = tdefl_flush_output_buffer(d));
2663
2664#if MINIZ_USE_UNALIGNED_LOADS_AND_STORES1 && MINIZ_LITTLE_ENDIAN1
2665 if (((d->m_flags & TDEFL_MAX_PROBES_MASK) == 1) &&
2666 ((d->m_flags & TDEFL_GREEDY_PARSING_FLAG) != 0) &&
2667 ((d->m_flags & (TDEFL_FILTER_MATCHES | TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_RAW_BLOCKS | TDEFL_RLE_MATCHES)) == 0))
2668 {
2669 if (!tdefl_compress_fast(d))
2670 return d->m_prev_return_status;
2671 }
2672 else
2673#endif // #if MINIZ_USE_UNALIGNED_LOADS_AND_STORES && MINIZ_LITTLE_ENDIAN
2674 {
2675 if (!tdefl_compress_normal(d))
2676 return d->m_prev_return_status;
2677 }
2678
2679 if ((d->m_flags & (TDEFL_WRITE_ZLIB_HEADER | TDEFL_COMPUTE_ADLER32)) && (pIn_buf))
2680 d->m_adler32 = (mz_uint32)mz_adler32(d->m_adler32, (const mz_uint8 *)pIn_buf, d->m_pSrc - (const mz_uint8 *)pIn_buf);
2681
2682 if ((flush) && (!d->m_lookahead_size) && (!d->m_src_buf_left) && (!d->m_output_flush_remaining))
2683 {
2684 if (tdefl_flush_block(d, flush) < 0)
2685 return d->m_prev_return_status;
2686 d->m_finished = (flush == TDEFL_FINISH);
2687 if (flush == TDEFL_FULL_FLUSH) { MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(d->m_hash)memset(&(d->m_hash), 0, sizeof(d->m_hash)); MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(d->m_next)memset(&(d->m_next), 0, sizeof(d->m_next)); d->m_dict_size = 0; }
2688 }
2689
2690 return (d->m_prev_return_status = tdefl_flush_output_buffer(d));
2691}
2692
2693tdefl_status tdefl_compress_buffer(tdefl_compressor *d, const void *pIn_buf, size_t in_buf_size, tdefl_flush flush)
2694{
2695 MZ_ASSERT(d->m_pPut_buf_func)((void) sizeof ((d->m_pPut_buf_func) ? 1 : 0), __extension__
({ if (d->m_pPut_buf_func) ; else __assert_fail ("d->m_pPut_buf_func"
, "/work/repo/external/CppMicroServices/third_party/miniz.c",
2695, __extension__ __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); })); return tdefl_compress(d, pIn_buf, &in_buf_size, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), flush);
2696}

2698tdefl_status tdefl_init(tdefl_compressor *d, tdefl_put_buf_func_ptr pPut_buf_func, void *pPut_buf_user, int flags)
2699{
2700 d->m_pPut_buf_func = pPut_buf_func; d->m_pPut_buf_user = pPut_buf_user;
2701 d->m_flags = (mz_uint)(flags); d->m_max_probes[0] = 1 + ((flags & 0xFFF) + 2) / 3; d->m_greedy_parsing = (flags & TDEFL_GREEDY_PARSING_FLAG) != 0;
2702 d->m_max_probes[1] = 1 + (((flags & 0xFFF) >> 2) + 2) / 3;
2703 if (!(flags & TDEFL_NONDETERMINISTIC_PARSING_FLAG)) MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(d->m_hash)memset(&(d->m_hash), 0, sizeof(d->m_hash));
2704 d->m_lookahead_pos = d->m_lookahead_size = d->m_dict_size = d->m_total_lz_bytes = d->m_lz_code_buf_dict_pos = d->m_bits_in = 0;
2705 d->m_output_flush_ofs = d->m_output_flush_remaining = d->m_finished = d->m_block_index = d->m_bit_buffer = d->m_wants_to_finish = 0;
2706 d->m_pLZ_code_buf = d->m_lz_code_buf + 1; d->m_pLZ_flags = d->m_lz_code_buf; d->m_num_flags_left = 8;
2707 d->m_pOutput_buf = d->m_output_buf; d->m_pOutput_buf_end = d->m_output_buf; d->m_prev_return_status = TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY;
2708 d->m_saved_match_dist = d->m_saved_match_len = d->m_saved_lit = 0; d->m_adler32 = 1;
2709 d->m_pIn_buf = NULL((void*)0); d->m_pOut_buf = NULL((void*)0);
2710 d->m_pIn_buf_size = NULL((void*)0); d->m_pOut_buf_size = NULL((void*)0);
2711 d->m_flush = TDEFL_NO_FLUSH; d->m_pSrc = NULL((void*)0); d->m_src_buf_left = 0; d->m_out_buf_ofs = 0;
2712 memset(&d->m_huff_count[0][0], 0, sizeof(d->m_huff_count[0][0]) * TDEFL_MAX_HUFF_SYMBOLS_0);
2713 memset(&d->m_huff_count[1][0], 0, sizeof(d->m_huff_count[1][0]) * TDEFL_MAX_HUFF_SYMBOLS_1);
2714 return TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY;
2715}

2717tdefl_status tdefl_get_prev_return_status(tdefl_compressor *d)
2718{
2719 return d->m_prev_return_status;
2720}

2722mz_uint32 tdefl_get_adler32(tdefl_compressor *d)

2724 return d->m_adler32;

2727mz_bool tdefl_compress_mem_to_output(const void *pBuf, size_t buf_len, tdefl_put_buf_func_ptr pPut_buf_func, void *pPut_buf_user, int flags)
2728{
2729 tdefl_compressor *pComp; mz_bool succeeded; if (((buf_len) && (!pBuf)) || (!pPut_buf_func)) return MZ_FALSE(0);
2730 pComp = (tdefl_compressor*)MZ_MALLOC(sizeof(tdefl_compressor))malloc(sizeof(tdefl_compressor)); if (!pComp) return MZ_FALSE(0);
2731 succeeded = (tdefl_init(pComp, pPut_buf_func, pPut_buf_user, flags) == TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY);
2732 succeeded = succeeded && (tdefl_compress_buffer(pComp, pBuf, buf_len, TDEFL_FINISH) == TDEFL_STATUS_DONE);
2733 MZ_FREE(pComp)free(pComp); return succeeded;
2734}
2735
2736typedef struct
2737{
2738 size_t m_size, m_capacity;
2739 mz_uint8 *m_pBuf;
2740 mz_bool m_expandable;
2741} tdefl_output_buffer;
2742
2743static mz_bool tdefl_output_buffer_putter(const void *pBuf, int len, void *pUser)
2744{
2745 tdefl_output_buffer *p = (tdefl_output_buffer *)pUser;
2746 size_t new_size = p->m_size + len;
2747 if (new_size > p->m_capacity)
2748 {
2749 size_t new_capacity = p->m_capacity; mz_uint8 *pNew_buf; if (!p->m_expandable) return MZ_FALSE(0);
2750 do { new_capacity = MZ_MAX(128U, new_capacity << 1U)(((128U)>(new_capacity << 1U))?(128U):(new_capacity <<
1U)); } while (new_size > new_capacity);
2751 pNew_buf = (mz_uint8*)MZ_REALLOC(p->m_pBuf, new_capacity)realloc(p->m_pBuf, new_capacity); if (!pNew_buf) return MZ_FALSE(0);
2752 p->m_pBuf = pNew_buf; p->m_capacity = new_capacity;
2753 }
2754 memcpy((mz_uint8*)p->m_pBuf + p->m_size, pBuf, len); p->m_size = new_size;
2755 return MZ_TRUE(1);
2756}
2757
2758void *tdefl_compress_mem_to_heap(const void *pSrc_buf, size_t src_buf_len, size_t *pOut_len, int flags)
2759{
2760 tdefl_output_buffer out_buf; MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(out_buf)memset(&(out_buf), 0, sizeof(out_buf));
2761 if (!pOut_len) return MZ_FALSE(0); else *pOut_len = 0;
2762 out_buf.m_expandable = MZ_TRUE(1);
2763 if (!tdefl_compress_mem_to_output(pSrc_buf, src_buf_len, tdefl_output_buffer_putter, &out_buf, flags)) return NULL((void*)0);
2764 *pOut_len = out_buf.m_size; return out_buf.m_pBuf;
2765}
2766
2767size_t tdefl_compress_mem_to_mem(void *pOut_buf, size_t out_buf_len, const void *pSrc_buf, size_t src_buf_len, int flags)
2768{
2769 tdefl_output_buffer out_buf; MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(out_buf)memset(&(out_buf), 0, sizeof(out_buf));
2770 if (!pOut_buf) return 0;
2771 out_buf.m_pBuf = (mz_uint8*)pOut_buf; out_buf.m_capacity = out_buf_len;
2772 if (!tdefl_compress_mem_to_output(pSrc_buf, src_buf_len, tdefl_output_buffer_putter, &out_buf, flags)) return 0;
2773 return out_buf.m_size;
2774}
2775
2776#ifndef MINIZ_NO_ZLIB_APIS
2777static const mz_uint s_tdefl_num_probes[11] = { 0, 1, 6, 32, 16, 32, 128, 256, 512, 768, 1500 };
2778
2779// level may actually range from [0,10] (10 is a "hidden" max level, where we want a bit more compression and it's fine if throughput to fall off a cliff on some files).
2780mz_uint tdefl_create_comp_flags_from_zip_params(int level, int window_bits, int strategy)
2781{
2782 mz_uint comp_flags = s_tdefl_num_probes[(level >= 0) ? MZ_MIN(10, level)(((10)<(level))?(10):(level)) : MZ_DEFAULT_LEVEL] | ((level <= 3) ? TDEFL_GREEDY_PARSING_FLAG : 0);
2783 if (window_bits > 0) comp_flags |= TDEFL_WRITE_ZLIB_HEADER;
2784
2785 if (!level) comp_flags |= TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_RAW_BLOCKS;
2786 else if (strategy == MZ_FILTERED) comp_flags |= TDEFL_FILTER_MATCHES;
2787 else if (strategy == MZ_HUFFMAN_ONLY) comp_flags &= ~TDEFL_MAX_PROBES_MASK;
2788 else if (strategy == MZ_FIXED) comp_flags |= TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_STATIC_BLOCKS;
2789 else if (strategy == MZ_RLE) comp_flags |= TDEFL_RLE_MATCHES;
2790
2791 return comp_flags;
2792}
2793#endif //MINIZ_NO_ZLIB_APIS

2795#ifdef _MSC_VER

2800// Simple PNG writer function by Alex Evans, 2011. Released into the public domain: https://gist.github.com/908299, more context at
2801// http://altdevblogaday.org/2011/04/06/a-smaller-jpg-encoder/.
2802// This is actually a modification of Alex's original code so PNG files generated by this function pass pngcheck.
2803void *tdefl_write_image_to_png_file_in_memory_ex(const void *pImage, int w, int h, int num_chans, size_t *pLen_out, mz_uint level, mz_bool flip)
2804{
2805 // Using a local copy of this array here in case MINIZ_NO_ZLIB_APIS was defined.
2806 static const mz_uint s_tdefl_png_num_probes[11] = { 0, 1, 6, 32, 16, 32, 128, 256, 512, 768, 1500 };
2807 tdefl_compressor *pComp = (tdefl_compressor *)MZ_MALLOC(sizeof(tdefl_compressor))malloc(sizeof(tdefl_compressor)); tdefl_output_buffer out_buf; int i, bpl = w * num_chans, y, z; mz_uint32 c; *pLen_out = 0;
2808 if (!pComp) return NULL((void*)0);
2809 MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(out_buf)memset(&(out_buf), 0, sizeof(out_buf)); out_buf.m_expandable = MZ_TRUE(1); out_buf.m_capacity = 57+MZ_MAX(64, (1+bpl)*h)(((64)>((1+bpl)*h))?(64):((1+bpl)*h)); if (NULL((void*)0) == (out_buf.m_pBuf = (mz_uint8*)MZ_MALLOC(out_buf.m_capacity)malloc(out_buf.m_capacity))) { MZ_FREE(pComp)free(pComp); return NULL((void*)0); }
2810 // write dummy header
2811 for (z = 41; z; --z) tdefl_output_buffer_putter(&z, 1, &out_buf);
2812 // compress image data
2813 tdefl_init(pComp, tdefl_output_buffer_putter, &out_buf, s_tdefl_png_num_probes[MZ_MIN(10, level)(((10)<(level))?(10):(level))] | TDEFL_WRITE_ZLIB_HEADER);
2814 for (y = 0; y < h; ++y) { tdefl_compress_buffer(pComp, &z, 1, TDEFL_NO_FLUSH); tdefl_compress_buffer(pComp, (mz_uint8*)pImage + (flip ? (h - 1 - y) : y) * bpl, bpl, TDEFL_NO_FLUSH); }
2815 if (tdefl_compress_buffer(pComp, NULL((void*)0), 0, TDEFL_FINISH) != TDEFL_STATUS_DONE) { MZ_FREE(pComp)free(pComp); MZ_FREE(out_buf.m_pBuf)free(out_buf.m_pBuf); return NULL((void*)0); }
2816 // write real header
2817 *pLen_out = out_buf.m_size-41;
2818 {
2819 static const mz_uint8 chans[] = {0x00, 0x00, 0x04, 0x02, 0x06};
2820 mz_uint8 pnghdr[41]={0x89,0x50,0x4e,0x47,0x0d,0x0a,0x1a,0x0a,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x0d,0x49,0x48,0x44,0x52,
2821 0,0,(mz_uint8)(w>>8),(mz_uint8)w,0,0,(mz_uint8)(h>>8),(mz_uint8)h,8,chans[num_chans],0,0,0,0,0,0,0,
2822 (mz_uint8)(*pLen_out>>24),(mz_uint8)(*pLen_out>>16),(mz_uint8)(*pLen_out>>8),(mz_uint8)*pLen_out,0x49,0x44,0x41,0x54};
2823 c=(mz_uint32)mz_crc32(MZ_CRC32_INIT(0),pnghdr+12,17); for (i=0; i<4; ++i, c<<=8) ((mz_uint8*)(pnghdr+29))[i]=(mz_uint8)(c>>24);
2824 memcpy(out_buf.m_pBuf, pnghdr, 41);
2825 }
2826 // write footer (IDAT CRC-32, followed by IEND chunk)
2827 if (!tdefl_output_buffer_putter("\0\0\0\0\0\0\0\0\x49\x45\x4e\x44\xae\x42\x60\x82", 16, &out_buf)) { *pLen_out = 0; MZ_FREE(pComp)free(pComp); MZ_FREE(out_buf.m_pBuf)free(out_buf.m_pBuf); return NULL((void*)0); }
2828 c = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(MZ_CRC32_INIT(0),out_buf.m_pBuf+41-4, *pLen_out+4); for (i=0; i<4; ++i, c<<=8) (out_buf.m_pBuf+out_buf.m_size-16)[i] = (mz_uint8)(c >> 24);
2829 // compute final size of file, grab compressed data buffer and return
2830 *pLen_out += 57; MZ_FREE(pComp)free(pComp); return out_buf.m_pBuf;
2831}
2832void *tdefl_write_image_to_png_file_in_memory(const void *pImage, int w, int h, int num_chans, size_t *pLen_out)
2833{
2834 // Level 6 corresponds to TDEFL_DEFAULT_MAX_PROBES or MZ_DEFAULT_LEVEL (but we can't depend on MZ_DEFAULT_LEVEL being available in case the zlib API's where #defined out)
2835 return tdefl_write_image_to_png_file_in_memory_ex(pImage, w, h, num_chans, pLen_out, 6, MZ_FALSE(0));
2836}

2857 // return NULL if inStr is NULL or if the conversion failed
2858 // The string returned is allocated using 'malloc' and hence should be de-allocated using 'free'.
2859 static wchar_t* utf8_to_wchar(const char* inStr)
2860 {
2861 wchar_t* wstr = NULL((void*)0);
2862 if (inStr)
2863 {
2864 int wchars_count = MultiByteToWideChar(CP_UTF8, 0, inStr, -1, NULL((void*)0), 0);
2865 if (wchars_count > 0)
2866 {
2867 wstr = MZ_MALLOC(sizeof(wchar_t)*(wchars_count))malloc(sizeof(wchar_t)*(wchars_count));
2868 }
2869 if ((wstr != NULL((void*)0)) && (MultiByteToWideChar(CP_UTF8, 0, inStr, -1, wstr, wchars_count) == 0))
2870 {
2871 MZ_FREE(wstr)free(wstr);
2872 wstr = NULL((void*)0);
2873 }
2874 }
2875 return wstr;
2876 }

2878 static FILE *mz_fopen(const char *pFilename, const char *pMode)
2879 {
2880 FILE* pFile = NULL((void*)0);
2881 wchar_t* pFilenameW = utf8_to_wchar(pFilename);
2882 wchar_t* pModeW = utf8_to_wchar(pMode);
2883 (void)_wfopen_s(&pFile, pFilenameW, pModeW);
2884 MZ_FREE(pFilenameW)free(pFilenameW);
2885 MZ_FREE(pModeW)free(pModeW);
2886 return pFile;
2887 }

2891 FILE* pFile = NULL((void*)0);

2893 wchar_t* pModeW = utf8_to_wchar(pMode);
2894 if (_wfreopen_s(&pFile, pFilenameW, pModeW, pStream))
2895 {
2896 pFile = NULL((void*)0);
2897 }
2898 MZ_FREE(pFilenameW)free(pFilenameW);
2899 MZ_FREE(pModeW)free(pModeW);
2900 return pFile;
2901 }

3042static MZ_FORCEINLINEinline __attribute__((__always_inline__)) mz_bool mz_zip_array_reserve(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_zip_array *pArray, size_t new_capacity, mz_uint growing)

3067#ifndef MINIZ_NO_TIME
3068static time_t mz_zip_dos_to_time_t(int dos_time, int dos_date)
3069{
3070 struct tm tm;
3071 memset(&tm, 0, sizeof(tm)); tm.tm_isdst = -1;
3072 tm.tm_year = ((dos_date >> 9) & 127) + 1980 - 1900; tm.tm_mon = ((dos_date >> 5) & 15) - 1; tm.tm_mday = dos_date & 31;
3073 tm.tm_hour = (dos_time >> 11) & 31; tm.tm_min = (dos_time >> 5) & 63; tm.tm_sec = (dos_time << 1) & 62;
3074 return mktime(&tm);
3075}
3076
3077static void mz_zip_time_to_dos_time(time_t time, mz_uint16 *pDOS_time, mz_uint16 *pDOS_date)
3078{
3079#ifdef _MSC_VER
3080 struct tm tm_struct;
3081 struct tm *tm = &tm_struct;
3082 errno_t err = localtime_s(tm, &time);
3083 if (err)
3084 {
3085 *pDOS_date = 0; *pDOS_time = 0;
3086 return;
3087 }
3088#else
3089 struct tm *tm = localtime(&time);
3090#endif
3091 *pDOS_time = (mz_uint16)(((tm->tm_hour) << 11) + ((tm->tm_min) << 5) + ((tm->tm_sec) >> 1));
3092 *pDOS_date = (mz_uint16)(((tm->tm_year + 1900 - 1980) << 9) + ((tm->tm_mon + 1) << 5) + tm->tm_mday);
3093}
3094#endif

3097static mz_bool mz_zip_get_file_modified_time(const char *pFilename, mz_uint16 *pDOS_time, mz_uint16 *pDOS_date)
3098{

3100 (void)pFilename; *pDOS_date = *pDOS_time = 0;

3103 // On Linux with x86 glibc, this call will fail on large files (>= 0x80000000 bytes) unless you compiled with _LARGEFILE64_SOURCE. Argh.
3104 if (MZ_FILE_STATstat(pFilename, &file_stat) != 0)
3105 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3106 mz_zip_time_to_dos_time(file_stat.st_mtimest_mtim.tv_sec, pDOS_time, pDOS_date);

3120static mz_bool mz_zip_reader_init_internal(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint32 flags)
3121{
3122 (void)flags;
3123 if ((!pZip) || (pZip->m_pState) || (pZip->m_zip_mode != MZ_ZIP_MODE_INVALID))
3124 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3125
3126 if (!pZip->m_pAlloc) pZip->m_pAlloc = def_alloc_func;
3127 if (!pZip->m_pFree) pZip->m_pFree = def_free_func;
3128 if (!pZip->m_pRealloc) pZip->m_pRealloc = def_realloc_func;
3129
3130 pZip->m_zip_mode = MZ_ZIP_MODE_READING;
3131 pZip->m_archive_size = 0;
3132 pZip->m_central_directory_file_ofs = 0;
3133 pZip->m_total_files = 0;
3134
3135 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pZip->m_pState = (mz_zip_internal_state *)pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, sizeof(mz_zip_internal_state))))
3136 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3137 memset(pZip->m_pState, 0, sizeof(mz_zip_internal_state));
3138 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_SET_ELEMENT_SIZE(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir, sizeof(mz_uint8))(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir)->m_element_size
= sizeof(mz_uint8);
3139 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_SET_ELEMENT_SIZE(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, sizeof(mz_uint32))(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets)->m_element_size
= sizeof(mz_uint32);
3140 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_SET_ELEMENT_SIZE(&pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets, sizeof(mz_uint32))(&pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets)->
m_element_size = sizeof(mz_uint32);
3141 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3142}
3143
3144static MZ_FORCEINLINEinline __attribute__((__always_inline__)) mz_bool mz_zip_reader_filename_less(const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir_array, const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir_offsets, mz_uint l_index, mz_uint r_index)
3145{
3146 const mz_uint8 *pL = &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(pCentral_dir_array, mz_uint8, MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(pCentral_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, l_index))((mz_uint8 *)((pCentral_dir_array)->m_p))[((mz_uint32 *)((
pCentral_dir_offsets)->m_p))[l_index]], *pE;
3147 const mz_uint8 *pR = &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(pCentral_dir_array, mz_uint8, MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(pCentral_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, r_index))((mz_uint8 *)((pCentral_dir_array)->m_p))[((mz_uint32 *)((
pCentral_dir_offsets)->m_p))[r_index]];
3148 mz_uint l_len = MZ_READ_LE16(pL + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pL + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)), r_len = MZ_READ_LE16(pR + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pR + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS));
3149 mz_uint8 l = 0, r = 0;
3150 pL += MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE; pR += MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE;
3151 pE = pL + MZ_MIN(l_len, r_len)(((l_len)<(r_len))?(l_len):(r_len));
3152 while (pL < pE)
3153 {
3154 if ((l = MZ_TOLOWER(*pL)((((*pL) >= 'A') && ((*pL) <= 'Z')) ? ((*pL) - 'A'
+ 'a') : (*pL))) != (r = MZ_TOLOWER(*pR)((((*pR) >= 'A') && ((*pR) <= 'Z')) ? ((*pR) - 'A'
+ 'a') : (*pR))))
3155 break;
3156 pL++; pR++;
3157 }
3158 return (pL == pE) ? (l_len < r_len) : (l < r);
3159}
3160
3161#define MZ_SWAP_UINT32(a, b)do { mz_uint32 t = a; a = b; b = t; } while (0) do { mz_uint32 t = a; a = b; b = t; } MZ_MACRO_ENDwhile (0)
3162
3163// Heap sort of lowercased filenames, used to help accelerate plain central directory searches by mz_zip_reader_locate_file(). (Could also use qsort(), but it could allocate memory.)
3164static void mz_zip_reader_sort_central_dir_offsets_by_filename(mz_zip_archive *pZip)
3165{
3166 mz_zip_internal_state *pState = pZip->m_pState;
3167 const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir_offsets = &pState->m_central_dir_offsets;
3168 const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir = &pState->m_central_dir;
3169 mz_uint32 *pIndices = &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, 0)((mz_uint32 *)((&pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets)
->m_p))[0];
3170 const int size = pZip->m_total_files;
3171 int start = (size - 2) >> 1, end;
3172 while (start >= 0)
3173 {
3174 int child, root = start;
3175 for ( ; ; )
3176 {
3177 if ((child = (root << 1) + 1) >= size)
3178 break;
3179 child += (((child + 1) < size) && (mz_zip_reader_filename_less(pCentral_dir, pCentral_dir_offsets, pIndices[child], pIndices[child + 1])));
3180 if (!mz_zip_reader_filename_less(pCentral_dir, pCentral_dir_offsets, pIndices[root], pIndices[child]))
3181 break;
3182 MZ_SWAP_UINT32(pIndices[root], pIndices[child])do { mz_uint32 t = pIndices[root]; pIndices[root] = pIndices[
child]; pIndices[child] = t; } while (0); root = child;
3183 }
3184 start--;
3185 }
3186
3187 end = size - 1;
3188 while (end > 0)
3189 {
3190 int child, root = 0;
3191 MZ_SWAP_UINT32(pIndices[end], pIndices[0])do { mz_uint32 t = pIndices[end]; pIndices[end] = pIndices[0]
; pIndices[0] = t; } while (0);
3192 for ( ; ; )
3193 {
3194 if ((child = (root << 1) + 1) >= end)
3195 break;
3196 child += (((child + 1) < end) && mz_zip_reader_filename_less(pCentral_dir, pCentral_dir_offsets, pIndices[child], pIndices[child + 1]));
3197 if (!mz_zip_reader_filename_less(pCentral_dir, pCentral_dir_offsets, pIndices[root], pIndices[child]))
3198 break;
3199 MZ_SWAP_UINT32(pIndices[root], pIndices[child])do { mz_uint32 t = pIndices[root]; pIndices[root] = pIndices[
child]; pIndices[child] = t; } while (0); root = child;
3200 }
3201 end--;
3202 }
3203}
3204
3205static mz_bool mz_zip_reader_read_central_dir(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint32 flags)
3206{
3207 mz_uint cdir_size, num_this_disk, cdir_disk_index;
3208 mz_uint64 cdir_ofs;
3209 mz_int64 cur_file_ofs;
3210 const mz_uint8 *p;
3211 mz_uint32 buf_u32[4096 / sizeof(mz_uint32)]; mz_uint8 *pBuf = (mz_uint8 *)buf_u32;
3212 mz_bool sort_central_dir = ((flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_DO_NOT_SORT_CENTRAL_DIRECTORY) == 0);
3213 mz_bool zip_signature_found = 0;
3214 // Basic sanity checks - reject files which are too small, and check the first 4 bytes of the file to make sure a local header is there.
3215 if (pZip->m_archive_size < MZ_ZIP_END_OF_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE)
3216 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3217 // Find the end of central directory record by scanning the file from the end towards the beginning.
3218 cur_file_ofs = MZ_MAX((mz_int64)pZip->m_archive_size - (mz_int64)sizeof(buf_u32), 0)((((mz_int64)pZip->m_archive_size - (mz_int64)sizeof(buf_u32
))>(0))?((mz_int64)pZip->m_archive_size - (mz_int64)sizeof
(buf_u32)):(0));
3219 for ( ; ; )
3220 {
3221 int i, n = (int)MZ_MIN(sizeof(buf_u32), pZip->m_archive_size - cur_file_ofs)(((sizeof(buf_u32))<(pZip->m_archive_size - cur_file_ofs
))?(sizeof(buf_u32)):(pZip->m_archive_size - cur_file_ofs)
);
3222 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pBuf, n) != (mz_uint)n)
3223 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3224 for (i = n - 4; i >= 0; --i)
3225 {
3226 if (MZ_READ_LE32(pBuf + i)*((const mz_uint32 *)(pBuf + i)) == MZ_ZIP_END_OF_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIG)
3227 {
3228 // Read and verify the end of central directory record.
3229 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs + i, pBuf, MZ_ZIP_END_OF_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE) != MZ_ZIP_END_OF_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE)
3230 continue;
3231 if ((MZ_READ_LE32(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_SIG_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_SIG_OFS)) != MZ_ZIP_END_OF_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIG) ||
3232 ((pZip->m_total_files = MZ_READ_LE16(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_TOTAL_ENTRIES_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_TOTAL_ENTRIES_OFS
))) != MZ_READ_LE16(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_NUM_ENTRIES_ON_DISK_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_NUM_ENTRIES_ON_DISK_OFS
))))
3233 continue;
3234 zip_signature_found = 1;
3235 break;
3236 }
3237 }
3238
3239 if (zip_signature_found)
3240 {
3241 cur_file_ofs += i;
3242 break;
3243 }
3244 if ((!cur_file_ofs) || (cur_file_ofs < MZ_ZIP_END_OF_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE))
3245 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3246
3247 cur_file_ofs = MZ_MAX(cur_file_ofs - (mz_int64)(sizeof(buf_u32) - 3), 0)(((cur_file_ofs - (mz_int64)(sizeof(buf_u32) - 3))>(0))?(cur_file_ofs
- (mz_int64)(sizeof(buf_u32) - 3)):(0));
3248 }
3249
3250 num_this_disk = MZ_READ_LE16(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_NUM_THIS_DISK_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_NUM_THIS_DISK_OFS));
3251 cdir_disk_index = MZ_READ_LE16(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_NUM_DISK_CDIR_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_NUM_DISK_CDIR_OFS));
3252 if (((num_this_disk | cdir_disk_index) != 0) && ((num_this_disk != 1) || (cdir_disk_index != 1)))
3253 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3254
3255 if ((cdir_size = MZ_READ_LE32(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_SIZE_OFS))) < pZip->m_total_files * MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE)
3256 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3257
3258 cdir_ofs = cur_file_ofs - cdir_size;
3259 if ((cdir_ofs + (mz_uint64)cdir_size) > pZip->m_archive_size)
3260 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3261
3262 pZip->m_central_directory_file_ofs = cdir_ofs;
3263
3264 pZip->m_archive_file_ofs = cdir_ofs - MZ_READ_LE32(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_OFS_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(pBuf + MZ_ZIP_ECDH_CDIR_OFS_OFS));
3265 if (pZip->m_archive_file_ofs > pZip->m_archive_size)
3266 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3267
3268 if (pZip->m_total_files)
3269 {
3270 mz_uint i, n;
3271
3272 // Read the entire central directory into a heap block, and allocate another heap block to hold the unsorted central dir file record offsets, and another to hold the sorted indices.
3273 if ((!mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir, cdir_size, MZ_FALSE(0))) ||
3274 (!mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, pZip->m_total_files, MZ_FALSE(0))))
3275 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3276
3277 if (sort_central_dir)
3278 {
3279 if (!mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets, pZip->m_total_files, MZ_FALSE(0)))
3280 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3281 }
3282
3283 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cdir_ofs, pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir.m_p, cdir_size) != cdir_size)
3284 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3285
3286 // Now create an index into the central directory file records, do some basic sanity checking on each record, and check for zip64 entries (which are not yet supported).
3287 p = (const mz_uint8 *)pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir.m_p;
3288 for (n = cdir_size, i = 0; i < pZip->m_total_files; ++i)
3289 {
3290 mz_uint total_header_size, comp_size, decomp_size, disk_index;
3291 if ((n < MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE) || (MZ_READ_LE32(p)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p)) != MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIG))
3292 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3293 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, i)((mz_uint32 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets
)->m_p))[i] = (mz_uint32)(p - (const mz_uint8 *)pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir.m_p);
3294 if (sort_central_dir)
3295 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, i)((mz_uint32 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets
)->m_p))[i] = i;
3296 comp_size = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS));
3297 decomp_size = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS));
3298 if (((!MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_METHOD_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_METHOD_OFS))) && (decomp_size != comp_size)) || (decomp_size && !comp_size) || (decomp_size == 0xFFFFFFFF) || (comp_size == 0xFFFFFFFF))
3299 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3300 disk_index = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DISK_START_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DISK_START_OFS));
3301 if ((disk_index != num_this_disk) && (disk_index != 1))
3302 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3303 if (((mz_uint64)MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_LOCAL_HEADER_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_LOCAL_HEADER_OFS)) + MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + comp_size) > pZip->m_archive_size)
3304 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3305 if ((total_header_size = MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)) + MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)) + MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMMENT_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMMENT_LEN_OFS))) > n)
3306 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3307 n -= total_header_size; p += total_header_size;
3308 }
3309 }
3310
3311 if (sort_central_dir)
3312 mz_zip_reader_sort_central_dir_offsets_by_filename(pZip);
3313
3314 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3315}
3316
3317mz_bool mz_zip_reader_init(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint64 size, mz_uint32 flags)
3318{
3319 if ((!pZip) || (!pZip->m_pRead))
3320 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3321 if (!mz_zip_reader_init_internal(pZip, flags))
3322 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3323 pZip->m_archive_size = size;
3324 if (!mz_zip_reader_read_central_dir(pZip, flags))
3325 {
3326 mz_zip_reader_end(pZip);
3327 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3328 }
3329 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3330}
3331
3332static size_t mz_zip_mem_read_func(void *pOpaque, mz_uint64 file_ofs, void *pBuf, size_t n)
3333{
3334 mz_zip_archive *pZip = (mz_zip_archive *)pOpaque;
3335 size_t s = (file_ofs >= pZip->m_archive_size) ? 0 : (size_t)MZ_MIN(pZip->m_archive_size - file_ofs, n)(((pZip->m_archive_size - file_ofs)<(n))?(pZip->m_archive_size
- file_ofs):(n));
3336 memcpy(pBuf, (const mz_uint8 *)pZip->m_pState->m_pMem + file_ofs, s);
3337 return s;
3338}
3339
3340mz_bool mz_zip_reader_init_mem(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const void *pMem, size_t size, mz_uint32 flags)
3341{
3342 if (!mz_zip_reader_init_internal(pZip, flags))
3343 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3344 pZip->m_archive_size = size;
3345 pZip->m_pRead = mz_zip_mem_read_func;
3346 pZip->m_pIO_opaque = pZip;
3347#ifdef __cplusplus
3348 pZip->m_pState->m_pMem = const_cast<void *>(pMem);
3349#else
3350 pZip->m_pState->m_pMem = (void *)pMem;
3351#endif
3352 pZip->m_pState->m_mem_size = size;
3353 if (!mz_zip_reader_read_central_dir(pZip, flags))
3354 {
3355 mz_zip_reader_end(pZip);
3356 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3357 }
3358 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3359}

3361#ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
3362static size_t mz_zip_file_read_func(void *pOpaque, mz_uint64 file_ofs, void *pBuf, size_t n)
3363{
3364 mz_zip_archive *pZip = (mz_zip_archive *)pOpaque;
3365 mz_int64 cur_ofs = MZ_FTELL64ftello(pZip->m_pState->m_pFile);
3366 if (((mz_int64)file_ofs < 0) || (((cur_ofs != (mz_int64)file_ofs)) && (MZ_FSEEK64fseeko(pZip->m_pState->m_pFile, (mz_int64)file_ofs, SEEK_SET0))))
3367 return 0;
3368 return MZ_FREADfread(pBuf, 1, n, pZip->m_pState->m_pFile);
3369}

3371mz_bool mz_zip_reader_init_file(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename, mz_uint32 flags)
3372{
3373 mz_uint64 file_size;
3374 MZ_FILEFILE *pFile = MZ_FOPEN(pFilename, "rb")fopen(pFilename, "rb");
3375 if (!pFile)
3376 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3377 if (MZ_FSEEK64fseeko(pFile, 0, SEEK_END2))
3378 {
3379 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pFile);
3380 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3381 }
3382 file_size = MZ_FTELL64ftello(pFile);
3383 if (!mz_zip_reader_init_internal(pZip, flags))
3384 {
3385 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pFile);
3386 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3387 }
3388 pZip->m_pRead = mz_zip_file_read_func;
3389 pZip->m_pIO_opaque = pZip;
3390 pZip->m_pState->m_pFile = pFile;
3391 pZip->m_archive_size = file_size;
3392 if (!mz_zip_reader_read_central_dir(pZip, flags))
3393 {
3394 mz_zip_reader_end(pZip);
3395 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3396 }
3397 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3398}

3405
3406static MZ_FORCEINLINEinline __attribute__((__always_inline__)) const mz_uint8 *mz_zip_reader_get_cdh(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index)
3407{
3408 if ((!pZip) || (!pZip->m_pState) || (file_index >= pZip->m_total_files) || (pZip->m_zip_mode != MZ_ZIP_MODE_READING))
3409 return NULL((void*)0);
3410 return &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir, mz_uint8, MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, file_index))((mz_uint8 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir)->
m_p))[((mz_uint32 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets
)->m_p))[file_index]];
3411}
3412
3413mz_bool mz_zip_reader_is_file_encrypted(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index)
3414{
3415 mz_uint m_bit_flag;
3416 const mz_uint8 *p = mz_zip_reader_get_cdh(pZip, file_index);
3417 if (!p)
3418 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3419 m_bit_flag = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_BIT_FLAG_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_BIT_FLAG_OFS));
3420 return (m_bit_flag & 1);
3421}
3422
3423mz_bool mz_zip_reader_is_file_a_directory(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index)
3424{
3425 mz_uint filename_len, external_attr;
3426 const mz_uint8 *p = mz_zip_reader_get_cdh(pZip, file_index);
3427 if (!p)
3428 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3429
3430 // First see if the filename ends with a '/' character.
3431 filename_len = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS));
3432 if (filename_len)
3433 {
3434 if (*(p + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + filename_len - 1) == '/')
3435 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3436 }
3437
3438 // Bugfix: This code was also checking if the internal attribute was non-zero, which wasn't correct.
3439 // Most/all zip writers (hopefully) set DOS file/directory attributes in the low 16-bits, so check for the DOS directory flag and ignore the source OS ID in the created by field.
3440 // FIXME: Remove this check? Is it necessary - we already check the filename.
3441 external_attr = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTERNAL_ATTR_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTERNAL_ATTR_OFS));
3442 if ((external_attr & 0x10) != 0)
3443 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3444
3445 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3446}
3447
3448mz_bool mz_zip_reader_file_stat(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, mz_zip_archive_file_stat *pStat)
3449{
3450 mz_uint n;
3451 const mz_uint8 *p = mz_zip_reader_get_cdh(pZip, file_index);
3452 if ((!p) || (!pStat))
3453 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3454
3455 // Unpack the central directory record.
3456 pStat->m_file_index = file_index;
3457 pStat->m_central_dir_ofs = MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, file_index)((mz_uint32 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets
)->m_p))[file_index];
3458 pStat->m_version_made_by = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_VERSION_MADE_BY_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_VERSION_MADE_BY_OFS));
3459 pStat->m_version_needed = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_VERSION_NEEDED_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_VERSION_NEEDED_OFS));
3460 pStat->m_bit_flag = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_BIT_FLAG_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_BIT_FLAG_OFS));
3461 pStat->m_method = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_METHOD_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_METHOD_OFS));
3462#ifndef MINIZ_NO_TIME
3463 pStat->m_time = mz_zip_dos_to_time_t(MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILE_TIME_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILE_TIME_OFS)), MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILE_DATE_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILE_DATE_OFS)));
3464#endif
3465 pStat->m_crc32 = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_CRC32_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_CRC32_OFS));
3466 pStat->m_comp_size = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS));
3467 pStat->m_uncomp_size = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS));
3468 pStat->m_internal_attr = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_INTERNAL_ATTR_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_INTERNAL_ATTR_OFS));
3469 pStat->m_external_attr = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTERNAL_ATTR_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTERNAL_ATTR_OFS));
3470 pStat->m_local_header_ofs = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_LOCAL_HEADER_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_LOCAL_HEADER_OFS));
3471
3472 // Copy as much of the filename and comment as possible.
3473 n = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)); n = MZ_MIN(n, MZ_ZIP_MAX_ARCHIVE_FILENAME_SIZE - 1)(((n)<(MZ_ZIP_MAX_ARCHIVE_FILENAME_SIZE - 1))?(n):(MZ_ZIP_MAX_ARCHIVE_FILENAME_SIZE
- 1));
3474 memcpy(pStat->m_filename, p + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE, n); pStat->m_filename[n] = '\0';
3475
3476 n = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMMENT_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMMENT_LEN_OFS)); n = MZ_MIN(n, MZ_ZIP_MAX_ARCHIVE_FILE_COMMENT_SIZE - 1)(((n)<(MZ_ZIP_MAX_ARCHIVE_FILE_COMMENT_SIZE - 1))?(n):(MZ_ZIP_MAX_ARCHIVE_FILE_COMMENT_SIZE
- 1));
3477 pStat->m_comment_size = n;
3478 memcpy(pStat->m_comment, p + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)) + MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)), n); pStat->m_comment[n] = '\0';
3479
3480 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3481}
3482
3483mz_uint mz_zip_reader_get_filename(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, char *pFilename, mz_uint filename_buf_size)
3484{
3485 mz_uint n;
3486 const mz_uint8 *p = mz_zip_reader_get_cdh(pZip, file_index);
3487 if (!p) { if (filename_buf_size) pFilename[0] = '\0'; return 0; }
3488 n = MZ_READ_LE16(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS));
3489 if (filename_buf_size)
3490 {
3491 n = MZ_MIN(n, filename_buf_size - 1)(((n)<(filename_buf_size - 1))?(n):(filename_buf_size - 1)
);
3492 memcpy(pFilename, p + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE, n);
3493 pFilename[n] = '\0';
3494 }
3495 return n + 1;
3496}
3497
3498static MZ_FORCEINLINEinline __attribute__((__always_inline__)) mz_bool mz_zip_reader_string_equal(const char *pA, const char *pB, mz_uint len, mz_uint flags)
3499{
3500 mz_uint i;
3501 if (flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_CASE_SENSITIVE)
3502 return 0 == memcmp(pA, pB, len);
3503 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
3504 if (MZ_TOLOWER(pA[i])((((pA[i]) >= 'A') && ((pA[i]) <= 'Z')) ? ((pA[
i]) - 'A' + 'a') : (pA[i])) != MZ_TOLOWER(pB[i])((((pB[i]) >= 'A') && ((pB[i]) <= 'Z')) ? ((pB[
i]) - 'A' + 'a') : (pB[i])))
3505 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3506 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3507}
3508
3509static MZ_FORCEINLINEinline __attribute__((__always_inline__)) int mz_zip_reader_filename_compare(const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir_array, const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir_offsets, mz_uint l_index, const char *pR, mz_uint r_len)
3510{
3511 const mz_uint8 *pL = &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(pCentral_dir_array, mz_uint8, MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(pCentral_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, l_index))((mz_uint8 *)((pCentral_dir_array)->m_p))[((mz_uint32 *)((
pCentral_dir_offsets)->m_p))[l_index]], *pE;
3512 mz_uint l_len = MZ_READ_LE16(pL + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pL + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS));
3513 mz_uint8 l = 0, r = 0;
3514 pL += MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE;
3515 pE = pL + MZ_MIN(l_len, r_len)(((l_len)<(r_len))?(l_len):(r_len));
3516 while (pL < pE)
3517 {
3518 if ((l = MZ_TOLOWER(*pL)((((*pL) >= 'A') && ((*pL) <= 'Z')) ? ((*pL) - 'A'
+ 'a') : (*pL))) != (r = MZ_TOLOWER(*pR)((((*pR) >= 'A') && ((*pR) <= 'Z')) ? ((*pR) - 'A'
+ 'a') : (*pR))))
3519 break;
3520 pL++; pR++;
3521 }
3522 return (pL == pE) ? (int)(l_len - r_len) : (l - r);
3523}
3524
3525static int mz_zip_reader_locate_file_binary_search(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename)
3526{
3527 mz_zip_internal_state *pState = pZip->m_pState;
3528 const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir_offsets = &pState->m_central_dir_offsets;
3529 const mz_zip_array *pCentral_dir = &pState->m_central_dir;
3530 mz_uint32 *pIndices = &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, 0)((mz_uint32 *)((&pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets)
->m_p))[0];
3531 const int size = pZip->m_total_files;
3532 const mz_uint filename_len = (mz_uint)strlen(pFilename);
3533 int l = 0, h = size - 1;
3534 while (l <= h)
3535 {
3536 int m = (l + h) >> 1, file_index = pIndices[m], comp = mz_zip_reader_filename_compare(pCentral_dir, pCentral_dir_offsets, file_index, pFilename, filename_len);
3537 if (!comp)
3538 return file_index;
3539 else if (comp < 0)
3540 l = m + 1;
3541 else
3542 h = m - 1;
3543 }
3544 return -1;
3545}
3546
3547int mz_zip_reader_locate_file(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pName, const char *pComment, mz_uint flags)
3548{
3549 mz_uint file_index; size_t name_len, comment_len;
3550 if ((!pZip) || (!pZip->m_pState) || (!pName) || (pZip->m_zip_mode != MZ_ZIP_MODE_READING))
3551 return -1;
3552 if (((flags & (MZ_ZIP_FLAG_IGNORE_PATH | MZ_ZIP_FLAG_CASE_SENSITIVE)) == 0) && (!pComment) && (pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets.m_size))
3553 return mz_zip_reader_locate_file_binary_search(pZip, pName);
3554 name_len = strlen(pName); if (name_len > 0xFFFF) return -1;
3555 comment_len = pComment ? strlen(pComment) : 0; if (comment_len > 0xFFFF) return -1;
3556 for (file_index = 0; file_index < pZip->m_total_files; file_index++)
3557 {
3558 const mz_uint8 *pHeader = &MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir, mz_uint8, MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_ELEMENT(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, mz_uint32, file_index))((mz_uint8 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir)->
m_p))[((mz_uint32 *)((&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets
)->m_p))[file_index]];
3559 mz_uint filename_len = MZ_READ_LE16(pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS));
3560 const char *pFilename = (const char *)pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE;
3561 if (filename_len < name_len)
3562 continue;
3563 if (comment_len)
3564 {
3565 mz_uint file_extra_len = MZ_READ_LE16(pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)), file_comment_len = MZ_READ_LE16(pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMMENT_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pHeader + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMMENT_LEN_OFS));
3566 const char *pFile_comment = pFilename + filename_len + file_extra_len;
3567 if ((file_comment_len != comment_len) || (!mz_zip_reader_string_equal(pComment, pFile_comment, file_comment_len, flags)))
3568 continue;
3569 }
3570 if ((flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_IGNORE_PATH) && (filename_len))
3571 {
3572 int ofs = filename_len - 1;
3573 do
3574 {
3575 if ((pFilename[ofs] == '/') || (pFilename[ofs] == '\\') || (pFilename[ofs] == ':'))
3576 break;
3577 } while (--ofs >= 0);
3578 ofs++;
3579 pFilename += ofs; filename_len -= ofs;
3580 }
3581 if ((filename_len == name_len) && (mz_zip_reader_string_equal(pName, pFilename, filename_len, flags)))
3582 return file_index;
3583 }
3584 return -1;
3585}
3586
3587mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_to_mem_no_alloc(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, void *pBuf, size_t buf_size, mz_uint flags, void *pUser_read_buf, size_t user_read_buf_size)
3588{
3589 int status = TINFL_STATUS_DONE;
3590 mz_uint64 needed_size, cur_file_ofs, comp_remaining, out_buf_ofs = 0, read_buf_size, read_buf_ofs = 0, read_buf_avail;
3591 mz_zip_archive_file_stat file_stat;
3592 void *pRead_buf;
3593 mz_uint32 local_header_u32[(MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + sizeof(mz_uint32) - 1) / sizeof(mz_uint32)]; mz_uint8 *pLocal_header = (mz_uint8 *)local_header_u32;
3594 tinfl_decompressor inflator;
3595
3596 if ((buf_size) && (!pBuf))
3597 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3598
3599 if (!mz_zip_reader_file_stat(pZip, file_index, &file_stat))
3600 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3601
3602 // Empty file, or a directory (but not always a directory - I've seen odd zips with directories that have compressed data which inflates to 0 bytes)
3603 if (!file_stat.m_comp_size)
3604 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3605
3606 // Entry is a subdirectory (I've seen old zips with dir entries which have compressed deflate data which inflates to 0 bytes, but these entries claim to uncompress to 512 bytes in the headers).
3607 // I'm torn how to handle this case - should it fail instead?
3608 if (mz_zip_reader_is_file_a_directory(pZip, file_index))
3609 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3610
3611 // Encryption and patch files are not supported.
3612 if (file_stat.m_bit_flag & (1 | 32))
3613 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3614
3615 // This function only supports stored and deflate.
3616 if ((!(flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA)) && (file_stat.m_method != 0) && (file_stat.m_method != MZ_DEFLATED8))
3617 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3618
3619 // Ensure supplied output buffer is large enough.
3620 needed_size = (flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA) ? file_stat.m_comp_size : file_stat.m_uncomp_size;
3621 if (buf_size < needed_size)
3622 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3623
3624 // Read and parse the local directory entry.
3625 cur_file_ofs = pZip->m_archive_file_ofs + file_stat.m_local_header_ofs;
3626 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pLocal_header, MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE) != MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE)
3627 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3628 if (MZ_READ_LE32(pLocal_header)*((const mz_uint32 *)(pLocal_header)) != MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIG)
3629 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3630
3631 cur_file_ofs += MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + MZ_READ_LE16(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS
)) + MZ_READ_LE16(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS
));
3632 if ((cur_file_ofs + file_stat.m_comp_size) > pZip->m_archive_size)
3633 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3634
3635 if ((flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA) || (!file_stat.m_method))
3636 {
3637 // The file is stored or the caller has requested the compressed data.
3638 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pBuf, (size_t)needed_size) != needed_size)
3639 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3640 return ((flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA) != 0) || (mz_crc32(MZ_CRC32_INIT(0), (const mz_uint8 *)pBuf, (size_t)file_stat.m_uncomp_size) == file_stat.m_crc32);
3641 }
3642
3643 // Decompress the file either directly from memory or from a file input buffer.
3644 tinfl_init(&inflator)do { (&inflator)->m_state = 0; } while (0);
3645
3646 if (pZip->m_pState->m_pMem)
3647 {
3648 // Read directly from the archive in memory.
3649 pRead_buf = (mz_uint8 *)pZip->m_pState->m_pMem + cur_file_ofs;
3650 read_buf_size = read_buf_avail = file_stat.m_comp_size;
3651 comp_remaining = 0;
3652 }
3653 else if (pUser_read_buf)
3654 {
3655 // Use a user provided read buffer.
3656 if (!user_read_buf_size)
3657 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3658 pRead_buf = (mz_uint8 *)pUser_read_buf;
3659 read_buf_size = user_read_buf_size;
3660 read_buf_avail = 0;
3661 comp_remaining = file_stat.m_comp_size;
3662 }
3663 else
3664 {
3665 // Temporarily allocate a read buffer.
3666 read_buf_size = MZ_MIN(file_stat.m_comp_size, MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE)(((file_stat.m_comp_size)<(MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE))?(file_stat
.m_comp_size):(MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE));
3667#ifdef _MSC_VER
3668 if (((0, sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32))) && (read_buf_size > 0x7FFFFFFF))
3669#else
3670 if (((sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32))) && (read_buf_size > 0x7FFFFFFF))
3671#endif
3672 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3673 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pRead_buf = pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, (size_t)read_buf_size)))
3674 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3675 read_buf_avail = 0;
3676 comp_remaining = file_stat.m_comp_size;
3677 }
3678
3679 do
3680 {
3681 size_t in_buf_size, out_buf_size = (size_t)(file_stat.m_uncomp_size - out_buf_ofs);
3682 if ((!read_buf_avail) && (!pZip->m_pState->m_pMem))
3683 {
3684 read_buf_avail = MZ_MIN(read_buf_size, comp_remaining)(((read_buf_size)<(comp_remaining))?(read_buf_size):(comp_remaining
));
3685 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pRead_buf, (size_t)read_buf_avail) != read_buf_avail)
3686 {
3687 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3688 break;
3689 }
3690 cur_file_ofs += read_buf_avail;
3691 comp_remaining -= read_buf_avail;
3692 read_buf_ofs = 0;
3693 }
3694 in_buf_size = (size_t)read_buf_avail;
3695 status = tinfl_decompress(&inflator, (mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf + read_buf_ofs, &in_buf_size, (mz_uint8 *)pBuf, (mz_uint8 *)pBuf + out_buf_ofs, &out_buf_size, TINFL_FLAG_USING_NON_WRAPPING_OUTPUT_BUF | (comp_remaining ? TINFL_FLAG_HAS_MORE_INPUT : 0));
3696 read_buf_avail -= in_buf_size;
3697 read_buf_ofs += in_buf_size;
3698 out_buf_ofs += out_buf_size;
3699 } while (status == TINFL_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT);
3700
3701 if (status == TINFL_STATUS_DONE)
3702 {
3703 // Make sure the entire file was decompressed, and check its CRC.
3704 if ((out_buf_ofs != file_stat.m_uncomp_size) || (mz_crc32(MZ_CRC32_INIT(0), (const mz_uint8 *)pBuf, (size_t)file_stat.m_uncomp_size) != file_stat.m_crc32))
3705 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3706 }
3707
3708 if ((!pZip->m_pState->m_pMem) && (!pUser_read_buf))
3709 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
3710
3711 return status == TINFL_STATUS_DONE;
3712}
3713
3714mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_file_to_mem_no_alloc(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename, void *pBuf, size_t buf_size, mz_uint flags, void *pUser_read_buf, size_t user_read_buf_size)
3715{
3716 int file_index = mz_zip_reader_locate_file(pZip, pFilename, NULL((void*)0), flags);
3717 if (file_index < 0)
3718 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3719 return mz_zip_reader_extract_to_mem_no_alloc(pZip, file_index, pBuf, buf_size, flags, pUser_read_buf, user_read_buf_size);
3720}
3721
3722mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_to_mem(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, void *pBuf, size_t buf_size, mz_uint flags)
3723{
3724 return mz_zip_reader_extract_to_mem_no_alloc(pZip, file_index, pBuf, buf_size, flags, NULL((void*)0), 0);
3725}
3726
3727mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_file_to_mem(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename, void *pBuf, size_t buf_size, mz_uint flags)
3728{
3729 return mz_zip_reader_extract_file_to_mem_no_alloc(pZip, pFilename, pBuf, buf_size, flags, NULL((void*)0), 0);
3730}
3731
3732void *mz_zip_reader_extract_to_heap(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, size_t *pSize, mz_uint flags)
3733{
3734 mz_uint64 comp_size, uncomp_size, alloc_size;
3735 const mz_uint8 *p = mz_zip_reader_get_cdh(pZip, file_index);
3736 void *pBuf;
3737
3738 if (pSize)
3739 *pSize = 0;
3740 if (!p)
3741 return NULL((void*)0);
3742
3743 comp_size = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS));
3744 uncomp_size = MZ_READ_LE32(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS)*((const mz_uint32 *)(p + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS));
3745
3746 alloc_size = (flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA) ? comp_size : uncomp_size;
3747#ifdef _MSC_VER
3748 if (((0, sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32))) && (alloc_size > 0x7FFFFFFF))
3749#else
3750 if (((sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32))) && (alloc_size > 0x7FFFFFFF))
3751#endif
3752 return NULL((void*)0);
3753 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pBuf = pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, (size_t)alloc_size)))
3754 return NULL((void*)0);
3755
3756 if (!mz_zip_reader_extract_to_mem(pZip, file_index, pBuf, (size_t)alloc_size, flags))
3757 {
3758 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
3759 return NULL((void*)0);
3760 }
3761
3762 if (pSize) *pSize = (size_t)alloc_size;
3763 return pBuf;
3764}
3765
3766void *mz_zip_reader_extract_file_to_heap(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename, size_t *pSize, mz_uint flags)
3767{
3768 int file_index = mz_zip_reader_locate_file(pZip, pFilename, NULL((void*)0), flags);
3769 if (file_index < 0)
3770 {
3771 if (pSize) *pSize = 0;
3772 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3773 }
3774 return mz_zip_reader_extract_to_heap(pZip, file_index, pSize, flags);
3775}
3776
3777mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_to_callback(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, mz_file_write_func pCallback, void *pOpaque, mz_uint flags)
3778{
3779 int status = TINFL_STATUS_DONE; mz_uint file_crc32 = MZ_CRC32_INIT(0);
3780 mz_uint64 read_buf_size, read_buf_ofs = 0, read_buf_avail, comp_remaining, out_buf_ofs = 0, cur_file_ofs;
3781 mz_zip_archive_file_stat file_stat;
3782 void *pRead_buf = NULL((void*)0); void *pWrite_buf = NULL((void*)0);
3783 mz_uint32 local_header_u32[(MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + sizeof(mz_uint32) - 1) / sizeof(mz_uint32)]; mz_uint8 *pLocal_header = (mz_uint8 *)local_header_u32;
3784
3785 if (!mz_zip_reader_file_stat(pZip, file_index, &file_stat))
3786 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3787
3788 // Empty file, or a directory (but not always a directory - I've seen odd zips with directories that have compressed data which inflates to 0 bytes)
3789 if (!file_stat.m_comp_size)
3790 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3791
3792 // Entry is a subdirectory (I've seen old zips with dir entries which have compressed deflate data which inflates to 0 bytes, but these entries claim to uncompress to 512 bytes in the headers).
3793 // I'm torn how to handle this case - should it fail instead?
3794 if (mz_zip_reader_is_file_a_directory(pZip, file_index))
3795 return MZ_TRUE(1);
3796
3797 // Encryption and patch files are not supported.
3798 if (file_stat.m_bit_flag & (1 | 32))
3799 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3800
3801 // This function only supports stored and deflate.
3802 if ((!(flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA)) && (file_stat.m_method != 0) && (file_stat.m_method != MZ_DEFLATED8))
3803 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3804
3805 // Read and parse the local directory entry.
3806 cur_file_ofs = file_stat.m_local_header_ofs;
3807 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pLocal_header, MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE) != MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE)
3808 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3809 if (MZ_READ_LE32(pLocal_header)*((const mz_uint32 *)(pLocal_header)) != MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIG)
3810 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3811
3812 cur_file_ofs += MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + MZ_READ_LE16(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_FILENAME_LEN_OFS
)) + MZ_READ_LE16(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS)*((const mz_uint16 *)(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS
));
3813 if ((cur_file_ofs + file_stat.m_comp_size) > pZip->m_archive_size)
3814 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3815
3816 // Decompress the file either directly from memory or from a file input buffer.
3817 if (pZip->m_pState->m_pMem)
3818 {
3819 pRead_buf = (mz_uint8 *)pZip->m_pState->m_pMem + cur_file_ofs;
3820 read_buf_size = read_buf_avail = file_stat.m_comp_size;
3821 comp_remaining = 0;
3822 }
3823 else
3824 {
3825 read_buf_size = MZ_MIN(file_stat.m_comp_size, MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE)(((file_stat.m_comp_size)<(MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE))?(file_stat
.m_comp_size):(MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE));
3826 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pRead_buf = pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, (size_t)read_buf_size)))
3827 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3828 read_buf_avail = 0;
3829 comp_remaining = file_stat.m_comp_size;
3830 }
3831
3832 if ((flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA) || (!file_stat.m_method))
3833 {
3834 // The file is stored or the caller has requested the compressed data.
3835 if (pZip->m_pState->m_pMem)
3836 {
3837#ifdef _MSC_VER
3838 if (((0, sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32))) && (file_stat.m_comp_size > 0xFFFFFFFF))
3839#else
3840 if (((sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32))) && (file_stat.m_comp_size > 0xFFFFFFFF))
3841#endif
3842 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3843 if (pCallback(pOpaque, out_buf_ofs, pRead_buf, (size_t)file_stat.m_comp_size) != file_stat.m_comp_size)
3844 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3845 else if (!(flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA))
3846 file_crc32 = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(file_crc32, (const mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf, (size_t)file_stat.m_comp_size);
3847 cur_file_ofs += file_stat.m_comp_size;
3848 out_buf_ofs += file_stat.m_comp_size;
3849 comp_remaining = 0;
3850 }
3851 else
3852 {
3853 while (comp_remaining)
3854 {
3855 read_buf_avail = MZ_MIN(read_buf_size, comp_remaining)(((read_buf_size)<(comp_remaining))?(read_buf_size):(comp_remaining
));
3856 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pRead_buf, (size_t)read_buf_avail) != read_buf_avail)
3857 {
3858 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3859 break;
3860 }
3861
3862 if (!(flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA))
3863 file_crc32 = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(file_crc32, (const mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf, (size_t)read_buf_avail);
3864
3865 if (pCallback(pOpaque, out_buf_ofs, pRead_buf, (size_t)read_buf_avail) != read_buf_avail)
3866 {
3867 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3868 break;
3869 }
3870 cur_file_ofs += read_buf_avail;
3871 out_buf_ofs += read_buf_avail;
3872 comp_remaining -= read_buf_avail;
3873 }
3874 }
3875 }
3876 else
3877 {
3878 tinfl_decompressor inflator;
3879 tinfl_init(&inflator)do { (&inflator)->m_state = 0; } while (0);
3880
3881 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pWrite_buf = pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, TINFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE32768)))
3882 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3883 else
3884 {
3885 do
3886 {
3887 mz_uint8 *pWrite_buf_cur = (mz_uint8 *)pWrite_buf + (out_buf_ofs & (TINFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE32768 - 1));
3888 size_t in_buf_size, out_buf_size = TINFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE32768 - (out_buf_ofs & (TINFL_LZ_DICT_SIZE32768 - 1));
3889 if ((!read_buf_avail) && (!pZip->m_pState->m_pMem))
3890 {
3891 read_buf_avail = MZ_MIN(read_buf_size, comp_remaining)(((read_buf_size)<(comp_remaining))?(read_buf_size):(comp_remaining
));
3892 if (pZip->m_pRead(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, pRead_buf, (size_t)read_buf_avail) != read_buf_avail)
3893 {
3894 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3895 break;
3896 }
3897 cur_file_ofs += read_buf_avail;
3898 comp_remaining -= read_buf_avail;
3899 read_buf_ofs = 0;
3900 }
3901
3902 in_buf_size = (size_t)read_buf_avail;
3903 status = tinfl_decompress(&inflator, (const mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf + read_buf_ofs, &in_buf_size, (mz_uint8 *)pWrite_buf, pWrite_buf_cur, &out_buf_size, comp_remaining ? TINFL_FLAG_HAS_MORE_INPUT : 0);
3904 read_buf_avail -= in_buf_size;
3905 read_buf_ofs += in_buf_size;
3906
3907 if (out_buf_size)
3908 {
3909 if (pCallback(pOpaque, out_buf_ofs, pWrite_buf_cur, out_buf_size) != out_buf_size)
3910 {
3911 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3912 break;
3913 }
3914 file_crc32 = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(file_crc32, pWrite_buf_cur, out_buf_size);
3915 if ((out_buf_ofs += out_buf_size) > file_stat.m_uncomp_size)
3916 {
3917 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3918 break;
3919 }
3920 }
3921 } while ((status == TINFL_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT) || (status == TINFL_STATUS_HAS_MORE_OUTPUT));
3922 }
3923 }
3924
3925 if ((status == TINFL_STATUS_DONE) && (!(flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_COMPRESSED_DATA)))
3926 {
3927 // Make sure the entire file was decompressed, and check its CRC.
3928 if ((out_buf_ofs != file_stat.m_uncomp_size) || (file_crc32 != file_stat.m_crc32))
3929 status = TINFL_STATUS_FAILED;
3930 }
3931
3932 if (!pZip->m_pState->m_pMem)
3933 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
3934 if (pWrite_buf)
3935 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pWrite_buf);
3936
3937 return status == TINFL_STATUS_DONE;
3938}

3940mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_file_to_callback(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename, mz_file_write_func pCallback, void *pOpaque, mz_uint flags)
3941{
3942 int file_index = mz_zip_reader_locate_file(pZip, pFilename, NULL((void*)0), flags);
3943 if (file_index < 0)
3944 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3945 return mz_zip_reader_extract_to_callback(pZip, file_index, pCallback, pOpaque, flags);
3946}

3948#ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
3949static size_t mz_zip_file_write_callback(void *pOpaque, mz_uint64 ofs, const void *pBuf, size_t n)
3950{
3951 (void)ofs; return MZ_FWRITEfwrite(pBuf, 1, n, (MZ_FILEFILE*)pOpaque);
3952}
3953
3954mz_bool mz_zip_reader_extract_to_file(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint file_index, const char *pDst_filename, mz_uint flags)
3955{
3956 mz_bool status;
3957 mz_zip_archive_file_stat file_stat;
3958 MZ_FILEFILE *pFile;
3959 if (!mz_zip_reader_file_stat(pZip, file_index, &file_stat))
3960 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3961 pFile = MZ_FOPEN(pDst_filename, "wb")fopen(pDst_filename, "wb");
3962 if (!pFile)
3963 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3964 status = mz_zip_reader_extract_to_callback(pZip, file_index, mz_zip_file_write_callback, pFile, flags);
3965 if (MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pFile) == EOF(-1))
3966 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3967#ifndef MINIZ_NO_TIME
3968 if (status)
3969 mz_zip_set_file_times(pDst_filename, file_stat.m_time, file_stat.m_time);
3970#endif
3971 return status;
3972}
3973#endif // #ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
3974
3975mz_bool mz_zip_reader_end(mz_zip_archive *pZip)
3976{
3977 if ((!pZip) || (!pZip->m_pState) || (!pZip->m_pAlloc) || (!pZip->m_pFree) || (pZip->m_zip_mode != MZ_ZIP_MODE_READING))
3978 return MZ_FALSE(0);
3979
3980 if (pZip->m_pState)
3981 {
3982 mz_zip_internal_state *pState = pZip->m_pState; pZip->m_pState = NULL((void*)0);
3983 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir);
3984 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir_offsets);
3985 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets);
3986
3987#ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
3988 if (pState->m_pFile)
3989 {
3990 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pState->m_pFile);
3991 pState->m_pFile = NULL((void*)0);
3992 }
3993#endif // #ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
3994
3995 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pState);
3996 }
3997 pZip->m_zip_mode = MZ_ZIP_MODE_INVALID;
3998
3999 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4000}

4004{

4006 if (file_index < 0)
4007 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4008 return mz_zip_reader_extract_to_file(pZip, file_index, pDst_filename, flags);
4009}

4012// ------------------- .ZIP archive writing

4015
4016static void mz_write_le16(mz_uint8 *p, mz_uint16 v) { p[0] = (mz_uint8)v; p[1] = (mz_uint8)(v >> 8); }
4017static void mz_write_le32(mz_uint8 *p, mz_uint32 v) { p[0] = (mz_uint8)v; p[1] = (mz_uint8)(v >> 8); p[2] = (mz_uint8)(v >> 16); p[3] = (mz_uint8)(v >> 24); }
4018#define MZ_WRITE_LE16(p, v)mz_write_le16((mz_uint8 *)(p), (mz_uint16)(v)) mz_write_le16((mz_uint8 *)(p), (mz_uint16)(v))
4019#define MZ_WRITE_LE32(p, v)mz_write_le32((mz_uint8 *)(p), (mz_uint32)(v)) mz_write_le32((mz_uint8 *)(p), (mz_uint32)(v))
4020
4021mz_bool mz_zip_writer_init(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint64 existing_size)
4022{
4023 if ((!pZip) || (pZip->m_pState) || (!pZip->m_pWrite) || (pZip->m_zip_mode != MZ_ZIP_MODE_INVALID))
4024 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4025
4026 if (pZip->m_file_offset_alignment)
4027 {
4028 // Ensure user specified file offset alignment is a power of 2.
4029 if (pZip->m_file_offset_alignment & (pZip->m_file_offset_alignment - 1))
4030 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4031 }
4032
4033 if (!pZip->m_pAlloc) pZip->m_pAlloc = def_alloc_func;
4034 if (!pZip->m_pFree) pZip->m_pFree = def_free_func;
4035 if (!pZip->m_pRealloc) pZip->m_pRealloc = def_realloc_func;
4036
4037 pZip->m_zip_mode = MZ_ZIP_MODE_WRITING;
4038 pZip->m_archive_size = existing_size;
4039 pZip->m_central_directory_file_ofs = 0;
4040 pZip->m_total_files = 0;
4041
4042 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pZip->m_pState = (mz_zip_internal_state *)pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, sizeof(mz_zip_internal_state))))
4043 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4044 memset(pZip->m_pState, 0, sizeof(mz_zip_internal_state));
4045 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_SET_ELEMENT_SIZE(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir, sizeof(mz_uint8))(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir)->m_element_size
= sizeof(mz_uint8);
4046 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_SET_ELEMENT_SIZE(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets, sizeof(mz_uint32))(&pZip->m_pState->m_central_dir_offsets)->m_element_size
= sizeof(mz_uint32);
4047 MZ_ZIP_ARRAY_SET_ELEMENT_SIZE(&pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets, sizeof(mz_uint32))(&pZip->m_pState->m_sorted_central_dir_offsets)->
m_element_size = sizeof(mz_uint32);
4048 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4049}
4050
4051static size_t mz_zip_heap_write_func(void *pOpaque, mz_uint64 file_ofs, const void *pBuf, size_t n)
4052{
4053 mz_zip_archive *pZip = (mz_zip_archive *)pOpaque;
4054 mz_zip_internal_state *pState = pZip->m_pState;
4055 mz_uint64 new_size = MZ_MAX(file_ofs + n, pState->m_mem_size)(((file_ofs + n)>(pState->m_mem_size))?(file_ofs + n):(
pState->m_mem_size));
4056#ifdef _MSC_VER
4057 if ((!n) || ((0, sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32)) && (new_size > 0x7FFFFFFF)))
4058#else
4059 if ((!n) || ((sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(mz_uint32)) && (new_size > 0x7FFFFFFF)))
4060#endif
4061 return 0;
4062 if (new_size > pState->m_mem_capacity)
4063 {
4064 void *pNew_block;
4065 size_t new_capacity = MZ_MAX(64, pState->m_mem_capacity)(((64)>(pState->m_mem_capacity))?(64):(pState->m_mem_capacity
)); while (new_capacity < new_size) new_capacity *= 2;
4066 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pNew_block = pZip->m_pRealloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pState->m_pMem, 1, new_capacity)))
4067 return 0;
4068 pState->m_pMem = pNew_block; pState->m_mem_capacity = new_capacity;
4069 }
4070 memcpy((mz_uint8 *)pState->m_pMem + file_ofs, pBuf, n);
4071 pState->m_mem_size = (size_t)new_size;
4072 return n;
4073}
4074
4075mz_bool mz_zip_writer_init_heap(mz_zip_archive *pZip, size_t size_to_reserve_at_beginning, size_t initial_allocation_size)
4076{
4077 pZip->m_pWrite = mz_zip_heap_write_func;
4078 pZip->m_pIO_opaque = pZip;
4079 if (!mz_zip_writer_init(pZip, size_to_reserve_at_beginning))
4080 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4081 if (0 != (initial_allocation_size = MZ_MAX(initial_allocation_size, size_to_reserve_at_beginning)(((initial_allocation_size)>(size_to_reserve_at_beginning)
)?(initial_allocation_size):(size_to_reserve_at_beginning))))
4082 {
4083 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pZip->m_pState->m_pMem = pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, initial_allocation_size)))
4084 {
4085 mz_zip_writer_end(pZip);
4086 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4087 }
4088 pZip->m_pState->m_mem_capacity = initial_allocation_size;
4089 }
4090 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4091}

4093#ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
4094static size_t mz_zip_file_write_func(void *pOpaque, mz_uint64 file_ofs, const void *pBuf, size_t n)
4095{
4096 mz_zip_archive *pZip = (mz_zip_archive *)pOpaque;
4097 mz_int64 cur_ofs = MZ_FTELL64ftello(pZip->m_pState->m_pFile);
4098 if (((mz_int64)file_ofs < 0) || (((cur_ofs != (mz_int64)file_ofs)) && (MZ_FSEEK64fseeko(pZip->m_pState->m_pFile, (mz_int64)file_ofs, SEEK_SET0))))
4099 return 0;
4100 return MZ_FWRITEfwrite(pBuf, 1, n, pZip->m_pState->m_pFile);
4101}
4102
4103mz_bool mz_zip_writer_init_file(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename, mz_uint64 size_to_reserve_at_beginning)
4104{
4105 MZ_FILEFILE *pFile;
4106 pZip->m_pWrite = mz_zip_file_write_func;
4107 pZip->m_pIO_opaque = pZip;
4108 if (!mz_zip_writer_init(pZip, size_to_reserve_at_beginning))
4109 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4110 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pFile = MZ_FOPEN(pFilename, "wb")fopen(pFilename, "wb")))
4111 {
4112 mz_zip_writer_end(pZip);
4113 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4114 }
4115 pZip->m_pState->m_pFile = pFile;
4116 if (size_to_reserve_at_beginning)
4117 {
4118 mz_uint64 cur_ofs = 0; char buf[4096]; MZ_CLEAR_OBJ(buf)memset(&(buf), 0, sizeof(buf));
4119 do
4120 {
4121 size_t n = (size_t)MZ_MIN(sizeof(buf), size_to_reserve_at_beginning)(((sizeof(buf))<(size_to_reserve_at_beginning))?(sizeof(buf
)):(size_to_reserve_at_beginning));
4122 if (pZip->m_pWrite(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_ofs, buf, n) != n)
4123 {
4124 mz_zip_writer_end(pZip);
4125 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4126 }
4127 cur_ofs += n; size_to_reserve_at_beginning -= n;
4128 } while (size_to_reserve_at_beginning);
4129 }
4130 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4131}
4132#endif // #ifndef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
4133
4134mz_bool mz_zip_writer_init_from_reader(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pFilename)
4135{
4136 mz_zip_internal_state *pState;
4137 if ((!pZip) || (!pZip->m_pState) || (pZip->m_zip_mode != MZ_ZIP_MODE_READING))
4138 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4139 // No sense in trying to write to an archive that's already at the support max size
4140 if ((pZip->m_total_files == 0xFFFF) || ((pZip->m_archive_size + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + MZ_ZIP_LOCAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE) > 0xFFFFFFFF))
4141 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4142
4143 pState = pZip->m_pState;
4144
4145 if (pState->m_pFile)
4146 {
4147#ifdef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
4148 pFilename; return MZ_FALSE(0);
4149#else
4150 // Archive is being read from stdio - try to reopen as writable.
4151 if (pZip->m_pIO_opaque != pZip)
4152 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4153 if (!pFilename)
4154 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4155 pZip->m_pWrite = mz_zip_file_write_func;
4156 if (NULL((void*)0) == (pState->m_pFile = MZ_FREOPEN(pFilename, "r+b", pState->m_pFile)freopen(pFilename, "r+b", pState->m_pFile)))
4157 {
4158 // The mz_zip_archive is now in a bogus state because pState->m_pFile is NULL, so just close it.
4159 mz_zip_reader_end(pZip);
4160 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4161 }
4162#endif // #ifdef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
4163 }
4164 else if (pState->m_pMem)
4165 {
4166 // Archive lives in a memory block. Assume it's from the heap that we can resize using the realloc callback.
4167 if (pZip->m_pIO_opaque != pZip)
4168 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4169 pState->m_mem_capacity = pState->m_mem_size;
4170 pZip->m_pWrite = mz_zip_heap_write_func;
4171 }
4172 // Archive is being read via a user provided read function - make sure the user has specified a write function too.
4173 else if (!pZip->m_pWrite)
4174 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4175
4176 // Start writing new files at the archive's current central directory location.
4177 pZip->m_archive_size = pZip->m_central_directory_file_ofs;
4178 pZip->m_zip_mode = MZ_ZIP_MODE_WRITING;
4179 pZip->m_central_directory_file_ofs = 0;
4180
4181 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4182}
4183
4184mz_bool mz_zip_writer_add_mem(mz_zip_archive *pZip, const char *pArchive_name, const void *pBuf, size_t buf_size, mz_uint level_and_flags)
4185{
4186 return mz_zip_writer_add_mem_ex(pZip, pArchive_name, pBuf, buf_size, NULL((void*)0), 0, level_and_flags, 0, 0);
4187}

4189typedef struct
4190{
4191 mz_zip_archive *m_pZip;
4192 mz_uint64 m_cur_archive_file_ofs;
4193 mz_uint64 m_comp_size;
4194} mz_zip_writer_add_state;
4195
4196static mz_bool mz_zip_writer_add_put_buf_callback(const void* pBuf, int len, void *pUser)
4197{
4198 mz_zip_writer_add_state *pState = (mz_zip_writer_add_state *)pUser;
4199 if ((int)pState->m_pZip->m_pWrite(pState->m_pZip->m_pIO_opaque, pState->m_cur_archive_file_ofs, pBuf, len) != len)

4273static mz_bool mz_zip_writer_validate_archive_name(const char *pArchive_name)
4274{
4275 // Basic ZIP archive filename validity checks: Valid filenames cannot start with a forward slash, cannot contain a drive letter, and cannot use DOS-style backward slashes.
4276 if (*pArchive_name == '/')
4277 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4278 while (*pArchive_name)
4279 {
4280 if ((*pArchive_name == '\\') || (*pArchive_name == ':'))
4281 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4282 pArchive_name++;
4283 }
4284 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4285}

4287static mz_uint mz_zip_writer_compute_padding_needed_for_file_alignment(mz_zip_archive *pZip)
4288{
4289 mz_uint32 n;
4290 if (!pZip->m_file_offset_alignment)
4291 return 0;
4292 n = (mz_uint32)(pZip->m_archive_size & (pZip->m_file_offset_alignment - 1));
4293 return (pZip->m_file_offset_alignment - n) & (pZip->m_file_offset_alignment - 1);
4294}

4296static mz_bool mz_zip_writer_write_zeros(mz_zip_archive *pZip, mz_uint64 cur_file_ofs, mz_uint32 n)
4297{
4298 char buf[4096];
4299 memset(buf, 0, MZ_MIN(sizeof(buf), n)(((sizeof(buf))<(n))?(sizeof(buf)):(n)));
4300 while (n)
4301 {
4302 mz_uint32 s = MZ_MIN(sizeof(buf), n)(((sizeof(buf))<(n))?(sizeof(buf)):(n));
4303 if (pZip->m_pWrite(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_file_ofs, buf, s) != s)
4304 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4305 cur_file_ofs += s; n -= s;
4306 }
4307 return MZ_TRUE(1);
4308}

4468 MZ_FILEFILE *pSrc_file = NULL((void*)0);
4469

4471 level_and_flags = MZ_DEFAULT_LEVEL;
4472 level = level_and_flags & 0xF;
4473

4475 return MZ_FALSE(0);

4477 return MZ_FALSE(0);

4479 return MZ_FALSE(0);

4489 return MZ_FALSE(0);

4495 if (!pSrc_file)
4496 return MZ_FALSE(0);

4501 if (uncomp_size > 0xFFFFFFFF)
4502 {

4504 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pSrc_file);

4506 }
4507 if (uncomp_size <= 3)
4508 level = 0;
4509

4522 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pSrc_file);
4523 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4524 }

4526
4527 if (uncomp_size)
4528 {

4531 if (!pRead_buf)
4532 {
4533 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pSrc_file);
4534 return MZ_FALSE(0);

4537 if (!level)

4539 while (uncomp_remaining)
4540 {

4545 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pSrc_file);

4547 }
4548 uncomp_crc32 = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(uncomp_crc32, (const mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf, n);
4549 uncomp_remaining -= n;
4550 cur_archive_file_ofs += n;
4551 }
4552 comp_size = uncomp_size;
4553 }
4554 else
4555 {
4556 mz_bool result = MZ_FALSE(0);

4559 if (!pComp)

4564 }

4567 state.m_cur_archive_file_ofs = cur_archive_file_ofs;

4569
4570 if (tdefl_init(pComp, mz_zip_writer_add_put_buf_callback, &state, tdefl_create_comp_flags_from_zip_params(level, -15, MZ_DEFAULT_STRATEGY)) != TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY)
4571 {
4572 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pComp);
4573 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
4574 MZ_FCLOSEfclose(pSrc_file);
4575 return MZ_FALSE(0);
4576 }
4577
4578 for ( ; ; )
4579 {
4580 size_t in_buf_size = (mz_uint32)MZ_MIN(uncomp_remaining, MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE)(((uncomp_remaining)<(MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE))?(uncomp_remaining

4584 break;
4585

4587 uncomp_remaining -= in_buf_size;
